Package: superassp
Type: Package
Title: A speech signal processing using various framworks using a wrassp-like interface
Version: 2.0.0
Date: 2026-04-08
Authors@R: c(
    person("Fredrik", "Nylén", , "fredrik.nylen@umu.se", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3373-0934"))
  )
Maintainer: Fredrik Nylén <fredrik.nylen@umu.se>
Description: This package bundles together routines to do speech or voice signal processing either continously througout the recording (trk_* functions),
  or produce acoustic summaries of a portion of the signal (lst_* functions). Example acoustic properties that can be tracked throughout the signal are f_o/ pitch tracking, for which seveal algorithms have been implmented, Formant frequencies and bandwidths, Harmonic-to-Noise, Harmonics and harmonic differences, Cepstral peak prominence, and numeours other. Several can be tracked at once using comprehensive assessment toolkits like Praat Sauce or Voice Sauce.
  Summary assessments (lst_ functions) include various toolkits for voice analysis, voice tremor analysis, and compreheninsive summaries using bottled openSMILE configurations. The results are for all functions either a 'wrassp' compliant AsspDataObj which may be stored to disc in an SSFF formated file, or a JSON format (JSTF) that more efficiently store dense spectral information related to a limited, but specific, portion of the signal.    
